Yesterday, we ordered dinner for four people to celebrate my daughter's birthday. When picking-up the food, we noticed one of the bags was about to tear, so we asked for it to be double bagged. The employee decided to re-bag the food. When we got home, some of our order was missing. We had to drive back another 15 minute ride because they do not deliver! The apology offered was empty and insincere. They could care less about satisfying a dissatisfied customer who spent over $100 based on the recommendation and reviews of others. Needless to say, it was very upsetting. I will not spend another dime with this business that does not value customer service. Lets see how their corporate office feels about this situation and what the response will be.The employee's command of the English language was inadequate. I suggest they put lids over the food, when not serving from the containers, because flies were in the building.  I gave a one star rating because the food was good, but that is ALL that was good.
